---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="Rainwater Catchment">
  <span class="page-tag">Water</span>
  <h1>Rainwater Catchment</h1>
  <p class="lead">Collection from house + porch roofs, storage, and 5-stage potable filtration.</p>

  <h2>Collection</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>House roof:</strong> 238 sq ft — metal standing seam. Gutter on low/interior side.</li>
    <li><strong>Porch roof:</strong> 224 sq ft — pitches away from house. Gutter on outer/yard edge.</li>
    <li><strong>Combined:</strong> ~462 sq ft. Both gutters pipe to shared storage.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Annual Capture (at 85% efficiency)</h2>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Location</th><th>Annual Rainfall</th><th>Capture</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Marshall, NC</td><td>~38"</td><td>~9,300 gal/yr</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Woodstock, NY</td><td>~56"</td><td>~13,700 gal/yr</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <p><strong>Estimated use:</strong> 30–50 gal/day for two people with composting toilet (no flush water) = 11,000–18,000 gal/yr. Rainwater covers 50–100% depending on location and conservation. Backup water source needed for dry spells.</p>

  <h2>System Flow</h2>

  <pre><code>House roof gutter ──┐
                    ├──► First flush diverter ──► (dirty water to ground)
Porch roof gutter ──┘           │
                                ▼
                         Leaf / debris screen
                                │
                                ▼
                    Storage tank (500–1,000 gal)
                    opaque, food-grade, sealed
                                │
                                ▼
                        12V pressure pump
                                │
                                ▼
                    ┌─── Potable filtration ───┐
                    │                          │
                    │  1. Spin-down (reusable)  │
                    │  2. Sediment (5–10 μm)    │
                    │  3. Carbon block (1–5 μm) │
                    │  4. 0.2 μm absolute       │
                    │  5. UV sterilizer (opt.)   │
                    │                          │
                    └──────────────────────────┘
                                │
                                ▼
                        House plumbing (potable)</code></pre>

  <h2>Potable Filtration Details</h2>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Stage</th><th>Function</th><th>Notes</th><th>Links</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>1. Spin-down</strong></td>
          <td>Catches coarse sediment</td>
          <td>Reusable, flush periodically. No cartridges.</td>
          <td></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>2. String/sediment</strong></td>
          <td>5–10 μm pre-filter</td>
          <td>Cheap cartridges. Protects downstream stages from clogging.</td>
          <td></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>3. Carbon block</strong></td>
          <td>1–5 μm. Chemicals, taste, odor</td>
          <td>Goes before 0.2μm so it's not fouling the finest filter.</td>
          <td></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>4. 0.2 μm absolute</strong></td>
          <td>Physically blocks bacteria &amp; protozoa</td>
          <td>Standard 10" inline housing. Key stage for potable.</td>
          <td>
            <a href="https://goblutech.com/products/0-2-micron-premium-water-filter-10-x-2-5-inch" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Blu Tech</a> ·
            <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Micron-Filter-10-Inch-Superior-Cartridge/dp/B0B61WX8M9" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Amazon</a> ·
            <a href="https://www.clearsourcerv.com/products/replacement-0-2-micron-filter" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ClearSource</a> ·
            <a href="https://www.watts.com/products/water-quality-rainwater-harvesting-solutions/water-quality-parts-accessories/filter-cartridges/ceramic-filters" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Watts ceramic</a>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>5. UV sterilizer</strong></td>
          <td>Final kill step for viruses</td>
          <td>Optional. Belt-and-suspenders for primary drinking water. Viruses are smaller than 0.2μm.</td>
          <td></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="note">
    <p><strong>Legal:</strong> NC is rainwater-friendly — no restrictions. Check Ulster County (Woodstock, NY) regulations for potable rainwater use.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="page-nav">
    <a href={`${base}envelope/`}>&larr; Envelope</a>
    <a href={`${base}electrical/`} class="next">Electrical &rarr;</a>
  </div>
</Layout>
